                    'software_description' => '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 3); font-family: Neuemontreal, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">This seminar will give you a strong working understanding of methods used to design and analyse single-case experimental design studies (i.e., n-of-1 trials, personalised trials, intrasubject, single-subjects, etc.) , including the assumptions underlying these methods and their limitations as well as their benefits. Demonstrations using real datasets will be incorporated together with hand-on exercise so that you will learn both the basic logic of single-case experiments and how to use them in your own research. In-depth interpretation of the obtained results will be made. An official ConsultantEdu, certificate of completion is provided at the conclusion of the seminar. For European PhD students, each seminar offers 2 ECTS.</span><br></p>',
                    'language_id' => 1,
